<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-13T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="910" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d910">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102 Tientsin/550: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Counselor of Embassy in China</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Peck</hi></persName>),
                                    <hi rend="italic">at Chungking</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-13T17:00:00-05:00">January 13, 1940—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5. Your 26, January 13, noon, in regard to silver at Tientsin.
                                Department approves your attitude as reported in the telegram under
                                reference. Department’s attitude is summarized in last two sentences
                                of paragraph 1 of its telegram No. 300, October 5, 7 p.m., to
                                    Tokyo.<note n="96" xml:id="d910fn96"><ref target="frus1939v04#pg_247"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                            Relations</hi>, 1939, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>,
                                        p. 247</ref>.</note> Department desires to avoid
                                participation in official discussion relating to the disposition of
                                the silver in question.</p>
                            <p>Sent to Chungking. Repeated to Peiping. Peiping please mail to
                                Tokyo.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>